sanitize term field "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
===================================================================

NAME
----

sanitize term field - Cleanse the field value in the term based on the context.

SYNOPSIS
--------

Cleanse the field value in the term based on the context.

Passing a term field value through the function should be assumed to
have cleansed the value for whatever context the term field is going to
be used.

If no context or an unsupported context is given, then default filters
will be applied.

There are enough filters for each context to support a custom filtering
without creating your own filter function. Simply create a function that
hooks into the filter you need.

USAGE
-----

` <?php sanitize_term_field( $field, $value, $term_id, $taxonomy, $context ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$field` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Term field to sanitize
    Default: *None*

 `$value` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Search for this term value
    Default: *None*

 `$term_id` 
:   ([*int*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Int "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Term ID
    Default: *None*

 `$taxonomy` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Taxonomy Name
    Default: *None*

 `$context` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Either edit, db, display, attribute, or js.
    Default: *None*

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `` `(mixed)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   sanitized field

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: [2.3](/Version_2.3 "Version 2.3")

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`sanitize_term_field()` is located in `wp-includes/taxonomy.php`

